President Obama has announced his intent to appoint several individuals to key administration posts. These include Jill Appell, C. Fred Bergsten, Bill Frenzel, Leo W. Gerard, Joseph T. Hansen, James P. Hoffa, Sandra Kennedy, David H. Long, Wade Randlett, Matthew Rubel, David H. Segura, Bryan Lourd, Barbara Goodman Manilow, Bryan Traubert, Lieutenant General Susan J. Helms, and Liza Gilbert. These individuals will be appointed to various committees and boards, such as the Advisory Committee for Trade Policy and Negotiations, the Board of Trustees of the John F. Kennedy Center for the Performing Arts, and the Board of Trustees of the Woodrow Wilson International Center for Scholars. President Obama expressed his gratitude for their dedication and looks forward to working with them in the future.